{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QAY4dXbKGAEh3rakJsSowS","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me generate a comprehensive final report summarizing all findings:\n\n## Comprehensive Analysis of Cloche's Self-Learning Cycle\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of the codebase, here's what I found:\n\n### 1. CODE THAT UPDATES PROMPT/SCRIPT FILES\n\n**File Writing Locations:**\n\n- **Prompt Updates:** `/workspace/internal/evolution/curator.go` (lines 17-59)\n  - `Curator.Apply()` reads target prompt file, sends to LLM with lesson for curation (ACE-style), then writes updated content back using `os.WriteFile()`\n  - Uses `AuditLogger.Snapshot()` to capture the original before modification\n  - File path is taken from `lesson.Target` (e.g., `.cloche/prompts/implement.md`)\n\n- **Script Generation:** `/workspace/internal/evolution/scriptgen.go` (lines 28-72)\n  - `ScriptGenerator.Generate()` creates new shell scripts based on lessons\n  - LLM returns JSON with `path` and `content` fields\n  - Writes executable script file with `os.WriteFile(fullPath, []byte(resp.Content), 0755)`\n  - Creates parent directories automatically with `os.MkdirAll()`\n\n- **Workflow File Updates:** `/workspace/internal/evolution/orchestrator.go` (lines 123-198)\n  - `handleNewStep()` modifies the workflow DSL file itself\n  - Reads workflow, generates step/wiring definitions, and writes back with `os.WriteFile(data.WorkflowPath, []byte(updated), 0644)`\n\n- **Knowledge Base Updates:** `/workspace/internal/evolution/audit.go` (lines 74-113)\n  - `AuditLogger.UpdateKnowledge()` appends lessons to `.cloche/evolution/knowledge/<workflow-name>.md`\n  - Creates the knowledge base file with header if it doesn't exist\n  - Appends lessons as markdown bullet points with ID, category, confidence, insight, action, and evidence\n\n- **Evolution Log:** `/workspace/internal/evolution/audit.go` (lines 18-41)\n  - `AuditLogger.Log()` appends JSON-L entries to `.cloche/evolution/log.jsonl`\n  - Records complete `EvolutionResult` with all changes made\n\n### 2. CODE THAT EDITS WORKFLOWS TO ADD STEPS AND WIRE THEM\n\n**Workflow Mutation System:** `/workspace/internal/dsl/mutator.go`\n\n- **`AddStep()` (lines 34-103)**\n  - Parses workflow DSL text and inserts new step definition\n  - Finds last step block's closing brace using regex `(?m)(^  \\})\\n`\n  - Builds step text with type-specific config (script's `run =`, agent's `prompt =`)\n  - Validates result by parsing with `Parse()` before returning\n  - Location: inserted after last step block, before wiring section\n\n- **`AddWiring()` (lines 105-127)**\n  - Appends new wire lines to workflow DSL\n  - Format: `from:result -> to`\n  - Inserts before workflow's closing brace\n  - Validates with `Parse()` to ensure correctness\n\n- **`UpdateCollect()` (lines 129-159)**\n  - Adds conditions to existing collect clauses\n  - Uses regex pattern to find collect clause targeting specific step\n  - Appends new step:result condition\n\n**Usage Flow:**\nIn `orchestrator.go` lines 165-184:\n1. `mutator.AddStep()` adds the new step definition from `lesson.StepType` (script or agent)\n2. `mutator.AddWiring()` wires new step: success → done, fail → abort\n3. Updated workflow written back to file\n\n### 3. WORKFLOW DSL PARSER AND VALIDATION\n\n**Parser:** `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go`\n\n- **Entry points:**\n  - `Parse()` - general parser with optional location hint\n  - `ParseForHost()` - for host.cloche files (LocationHost)\n  - `ParseForContainer()` - for container workflows (LocationContainer)\n  - `ParseAllForHost()` - parses multiple workflows in host.cloche\n\n- **Grammar elements parsed:**\n  - Workflow blocks with steps, wiring, and collect clauses\n  - Steps (name, type: agent/script/workflow, config, results)\n  - Wires (from:result -> to with optional output mappings)\n  - Collects (all/any conditions with target step)\n\n**Validation:** `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go` lines 145-242\n\n- **`Workflow.Validate()` (lines 145-229)** - comprehensive validation\n  - Checks entry step exists\n  - **Unlinked node detection (lines 153-212):**\n    - Builds `wired` map tracking which step results are wired\n    - Builds `reachable` set tracking steps reachable from entry\n    - For each step's result: `if !wired[name][result]` → error: \"step X result Y is not wired\"\n    - For each step: `if !reachable[name]` → error: \"step X is orphaned (unreachable)\"\n  - Validates all wire/collect targets exist\n  - Validates all results declared on referenced steps\n  - Checks for duplicate output mapping env vars\n\n- **`ValidateLocation()` (lines 231-242)** - ensures step types match location\n  - Only host workflows (LocationHost) can have `workflow_name` steps\n  - Container workflows cannot use `workflow_name`\n\n- **`ValidateConfig()` (lines 259-276)** - warns about unrecognized config keys\n\n### 4. COMPLETE SELF-LEARNING PIPELINE\n\n**Orchestrator:** `/workspace/internal/evolution/orchestrator.go` (lines 35-121)\n\n```\nStage 1: Collect\n  ↓ CollectedData (runs, captures, knowledge base, current prompts, workflow)\nStage 2: Classify\n  ↓ Classification (bug/feature/feedback/enhancement/chore)\nStage 3: Reflect\n  ↓ Lessons (each with category, target, insight, confidence)\nStage 4: Branch by category\n  - \"prompt_improvement\" → Curator.Apply() → writes .cloche/prompts/*.md\n  - \"new_step\" → ScriptGenerator.Generate() → writes .cloche/scripts/*.sh\n                → Mutator.AddStep/AddWiring() → writes .cloche/*.cloche\nStage 5: Audit\n  ↓ Log evolution result\n  ↓ Update knowledge base\n  ↓ Create snapshots of modified files\n```\n\n**Key Data Types:**\n\n- `Lesson` (lines 26-36 of types.go): id, category, step_type, target, insight, suggested_action, evidence, confidence\n- `EvolutionResult` (lines 38-48): records all changes made\n- `Change` (lines 50-56): type (add_script/add_step/prompt_update), file, reason, snapshot\n\n**LLM Integration:** `/workspace/internal/evolution/llmclient.go`\n\n- `CommandLLMClient.Complete()` - invokes shell command with prompt via stdin\n- Each stage sends system + user prompt to LLM\n- Responses are JSON (parsed and validated)\n\n**Evolution Trigger:** `/workspace/internal/evolution/trigger.go`\n\n- `Trigger.Fire()` debounces evolution runs per project+workflow (30 sec default)\n- Fires from gRPC server when run completes (`/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` line 350)\n- Calls `Orchestrator.Run()` asynchronously\n\n### 5. KNOWLEDGE PERSISTENCE\n\n**Knowledge Base Structure:**\n- Location: `.cloche/evolution/knowledge/<workflow-name>.md`\n- Format: Markdown with lessons as bullet points\n- Each lesson includes: ID, category, confidence, insight, action, evidence\n\n**Snapshots:**\n- Location: `.cloche/evolution/snapshots/`\n- Naming: `YYYYMMDDTHHMMSS-<filename>`\n- Captures file state before modification for audit trail\n\n**Evolution Log:**\n- Location: `.cloche/evolution/log.jsonl`\n- Format: JSON-L (one entry per line)\n- Complete record of each evolution pass with all changes\n\n### 6. ENTRY POINTS IN INTEGRATION\n\n- **Daemon startup:** `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go` lines 149-186\n  - `initEvolution()` creates trigger if enabled in config\n  - Trigger attached to gRPC server via `SetEvolution()`\n  \n- **Trigger activation:** When container run completes (successful or failed)\n  - Server calls `evolution.Fire(projectDir, workflowName, runID)`\n  - Trigger debounces and calls `Orchestrator.Run()`\n\n**File Paths (Absolute):**\n\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/orchestrator.go` - pipeline orchestration & workflow mutation\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/curator.go` - prompt file updates\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/scriptgen.go` - script file generation\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/reflector.go` - lesson extraction from runs\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/collector.go` - gathers input data\n- `/workspa