r\n\tSteps     map[string]*Step      // keyed by step name\n\tWiring    []Wire                // all wire declarations\n\tCollects  []Collect             // parallel convergence rules\n\tEntryStep string                // first step to execute\n\tConfig    map[string]string     // workflow-level config (container.image, etc.)\n}\n```\n\n**Workflow Locations:**\n```go\nconst (\n\tLocationContainer = \"container\"  // .cloche/*.cloche (except host.cloche)\n\tLocationHost      = \"host\"       // .cloche/host.cloche only\n)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. PARSING FLOW\n\n**parseWorkflow()** - Main entry point:\n1. Expects `workflow \"name\" {`\n2. Loops through workflow body, parsing:\n   - **Steps**: `step NAME { ... }` (type inferred from content)\n   - **Wires**: `STEP:RESULT -> TARGET [MAPPINGS]`\n   - **Collects**: `collect all/any(STEP:RESULT, ...) -> TARGET`\n   - **Config blocks**: `container { key = value }` or `host { key = value }`\n3. Sets `EntryStep` to first parsed step\n4. Returns validated workflow\n\n**parseStep()** - Step definition parsing:\n1. Expects `step NAME { ... }`\n2. Parses step fields recursively:\n   - `prompt = \"...\"` or `prompt = file(\"path\")`\n   - `run = \"...\"`\n   - `workflow_name = \"...\"`\n   - `results = [success, fail]`\n   - `container { ... }` or `host { ... }` blocks for nested config\n   - Other config keys (timeout, max_attempts, agent_command, etc.)\n3. **Infers type** from exactly one of `prompt`, `run`, or `workflow_name`\n4. Returns error if ambiguous or missing\n\n**parseWire()** - Wire declaration parsing:\n1. Expects `STEP:RESULT -> TARGET [MAPPINGS]`\n2. Optionally parses output mappings in `[KEY = output.path, ...]`\n3. **parseOutputPath()** recursively parses path expressions\n\n**parseCollect()** - Parallel convergence parsing:\n1. Expects `collect all|any(STEP:RESULT, STEP:RESULT, ...) -> TARGET`\n2. Collects can target regular steps or `done`/`abort`\n\n---\n\n### 5. VALIDATION LOGIC\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go` - `Workflow.Validate()` method\n\nThe validator performs five checks:\n\n**Check 1: Entry Step Exists**\n- Ensures `EntryStep` is not empty\n- Ensures `EntryStep` refers to an existing step\n\n**Check 2: Every Result is Wired**\n- For each step and its declared results:\n  - Ensures at least one wire OR one collect condition handles it\n  - Returns error if unwired result found\n- This prevents \"dangling\" results\n\n**Check 3: No Orphaned Steps**\n- Builds reachability map starting from `EntryStep`\n- Wires and collects add targets to reachable set\n- Returns error if any step is unreachable\n\n**Check 4: Collect Validation**\n- Validates target steps exist (or are `done`/`abort`)\n- Validates referenced steps exist\n- Validates referenced results are declared on those steps\n- Marks results as \"wired\" via collects\n\n**Check 5: Duplicate Output Mapping Keys**\n- For each wire targeting the same step:\n  - Checks no two wires map the same env var key\n  - Allows same key on wires to different steps\n  - Returns error on conflict\n\n**Check 6 (Special): Location Validation**\n- `ValidateLocation()` checks that `workflow_name` steps only appear in host workflows\n- Returns error if container workflow has `workflow_name` step\n\n**Check 7: Config Key Validation**\n- `ValidateConfig()` warns about unrecognized config keys (typos)\n- Known keys: prompt, run, workflow_name, timeout, max_attempts, agent_command, agent_args, results, feedback, prompt_step\n- Allows `container.*` and `host.*` prefixed keys\n\n---\n\n### 6. STEP TYPE INFERENCE\n\nThe parser determines step type from mutually exclusive fields:\n\n```\nprompt = \"...\" or prompt = file(\"...\")     → StepTypeAgent\nrun = \"...\"                                 → StepTypeScript\nworkflow_name = \"...\"                      → StepTypeWorkflow\n\nError if:\n- More than one of above present\n- None of above present\n- workflow_name in container workflow (location-specific error)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 7. WORKFLOW GRAPH TRAVERSAL\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/engine/engine.go`\n\nThe execution engine walks the workflow graph:\n\n**NextSteps(stepName, result) -> []string**\n- Returns all wired target steps for a given (step, result) pair\n- Supports **fanout** - multiple targets for parallel execution\n- Returns error if no wire found (unless a collect handles it)\n\n**Execution Model:**\n1. Launch entry step (concurrent goroutine)\n2. Wait for step completion in event loop\n3. For each step result:\n   - Call `wf.NextSteps(stepName, result)` to get targets\n   - Launch target steps concurrently\n   - Handle `done` and `abort` built-in terminals\n   - Process collect conditions (track satisfied conditions)\n4. Fire collect when conditions met (CollectAll = all satisfied, CollectAny = any satisfied)\n5. Continue until all branches reach `done`/`abort`\n\n---\n\n### 8. PROGRAMMATIC WORKFLOW MODIFICATION\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/dsl/mutator.go`\n\nThe mutator provides three operations:\n\n**AddStep(input, StepDef) -> string**\n- Inserts new step definition into workflow DSL text\n- Finds last step block's closing brace\n- Inserts new step before wiring section\n- Validates result parses successfully\n\n**AddWiring(input, []WireDef) -> string**\n- Appends wire lines to workflow\n- Inserts before workflow closing brace\n- Validates result parses successfully\n\n**UpdateCollect(input, CollectAddition) -> string**\n- Finds existing `collect` clause by target\n- Adds new condition to existing collect\n- Uses regex pattern matching for insertion point\n- Validates result parses successfully\n\nAll mutations re-parse to ensure validity.\n\n---\n\n### 9. PARSING ENTRY POINTS (INTEGRATION)\n\nThe parser is used in:\n\n- **`internal/agent/runner.go`** - Container agent parses its workflow\n- **`internal/adapters/web/handler.go`** - Web API parses uploaded workflows\n- **`internal/host/executor.go`** - Host executor loads workflows (via calling code)\n\n---\n\n### 10. CONCRETE EXAMPLE WORKFLOW\n\nFrom `/workspace/examples/hello-world/build.cloche`:\n\n```\nworkflow \"hello-world\" {\n  step init {\n    run = \"echo 'Initializing...'\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step generate {\n    run = \"echo '<html>...' > src/index.html\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step build {\n    run = \"cp src/index.html dist/index.html\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  init:success -> generate      // wire: if init succeeds, launch generate\n  init:fail -> abort            // wire: if init fails, abort workflow\n\n  generate:success -> build     // fanout possible here\n  generate:fail -> abort\n\n  build:success -> verify       // chaining\n  build:fail -> abort\n\n  verify:success -> done        // terminal\n  verify:fail -> build          // loop back\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 11. KEY FILES SUMMARY\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go` | Recursive descent parser, 573 lines |\n| `/workspace/internal/dsl/lexer.go` | Tokenizer with line/col tracking, 196 lines |\n| `/workspace/internal/dsl/token.go` | Token type definitions, 69 lines |\n| `/workspace/internal/dsl/mutator.go` | Programmatic DSL modification, 160 lines |\n| `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go` | Domain model + validation, 301 lines |\n| `/workspace/internal/domain/output_path_test.go` | OutputPath.Evaluate tests, 212 lines |\n| `/workspace/internal/engine/engine.go` | Graph execution engine, 312 lines |\n| `/workspace/docs/workflows.md` | DSL specification, 257 lines |\n\n---\n\n### 12. VALIDATION SUMMARY TABLE\n\n| Check | Error | Pass |\n|-------|-------|------|\n| Entry step exists | \"no entry step defined\" | Step exists and reachable |\n| All results wired | \"result is not wired\" | Every result has wire or collect |\n| No orphaned steps | \"step is orphaned (unreachable)\" | All steps reachable from entry |\n| Collect targets valid | \"collect target step not found\" | Targets exist or are terminals |\n| Collect refs valid | \"collect references unknown step\" | Steps & results exist |\n| Duplicate output mappings | \"duplicate output mapping for env var X targeting step Y\" | No conflicts |\n| Location constraints | \"workflow_name only in host workflows\" | Type matches location |\n| Config keys | Warnings only | Known keys or container.*/host.* prefixed |\n\n---\n\nThis architecture elegantly separates concerns:\n- **Lexer**: tokenization\n- **Parser**: syntax tree construction\n- **Domain Model**: semantic representation\n- **Validator**: graph consistency checking\n- **Engine**: execution with concurrency support\n- **Mutator**: DSL-level modifications for self-evolution\n\nThe design makes it straightforward to add new steps, rewire connections, and validate before execution."}],"totalDurationMs":58010,"totalTokens":68868,"totalToolUseCount":31,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":495,"cache_read_input_tokens":64863,"output_tokens":3508,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":495},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
