{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WM3Gxt6EedMCmWRtuusxBS","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package evolution\n     2→\n     3→import (\n     4→\t\"context\"\n     5→\n     6→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/domain\"\n     7→)\n     8→\n     9→// LLMClient abstracts LLM calls for evolution stages.\n    10→type LLMClient interface {\n    11→\tComplete(ctx context.Context, systemPrompt, userPrompt string) (string, error)\n    12→}\n    13→\n    14→// CollectedData is the input to the Classifier and Reflector.\n    15→type CollectedData struct {\n    16→\tRuns            []*domain.Run\n    17→\tCaptures        map[string][]*domain.StepExecution // run_id -> step executions\n    18→\tKnowledgeBase   string                             // contents of knowledge/<workflow>.md\n    19→\tCurrentPrompts  map[string]string                  // relative path -> content\n    20→\tCurrentWorkflow string                             // .cloche file content\n    21→\tWorkflowPath    string                             // path to .cloche file\n    22→\tProjectDir      string\n    23→\tWorkflowName    string\n    24→}\n    25→\n    26→// Lesson is a structured insight extracted by the Reflector.\n    27→type Lesson struct {\n    28→\tID              string   `json:\"id\"`\n    29→\tCategory        string   `json:\"category\"`\n    30→\tStepType        string   `json:\"step_type,omitempty\"`\n    31→\tTarget          string   `json:\"target,omitempty\"`\n    32→\tInsight         string   `json:\"insight\"`\n    33→\tSuggestedAction string   `json:\"suggested_action\"`\n    34→\tEvidence        []string `json:\"evidence\"`\n    35→\tConfidence      string   `json:\"confidence\"`\n    36→}\n    37→\n    38→// EvolutionResult records what an evolution pass produced.\n    39→type EvolutionResult struct {\n    40→\tID             string   `json:\"id\"`\n    41→\tProjectDir     string   `json:\"project_dir\"`\n    42→\tWorkflowName   string   `json:\"workflow_name\"`\n    43→\tTriggerRunID   string   `json:\"trigger_run_id\"`\n    44→\tTimestamp      string   `json:\"timestamp\"`\n    45→\tClassification string   `json:\"classification\"`\n    46→\tChanges        []Change `json:\"changes\"`\n    47→\tKnowledgeDelta string   `json:\"knowledge_delta\"`\n    48→}\n    49→\n    50→// Change describes a single file modification made by evolution.\n    51→type Change struct {\n    52→\tType     string `json:\"type\"`\n    53→\tFile     string `json:\"file\"`\n    54→\tReason   string `json:\"reason\"`\n    55→\tSnapshot string `json:\"snapshot\"`\n    56→}\n    57→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0d459df6-6a73-41bb-9a61-5157dd36e9c2","uuid":"eaefa7c5-9a93-42e8-8116-62443f74bfd7","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/internal/evolution/types.go","content":"package evolution\n\nimport (\n\t\"context\"\n\n\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/domain\"\n)\n\n// LLMClient abstracts LLM calls for evolution stages.\ntype LLMClient interface {\n\tComplete(ctx context.Context, systemPrompt, userPrompt string) (string, error)\n}\n\n// CollectedData is the input to the Classifier and Reflector.\ntype CollectedData struct {\n\tRuns            []*domain.Run\n\tCaptures        map[string][]*domain.StepExecution // run_id -> step executions\n\tKnowledgeBase   string                             // contents of knowledge/<workflow>.md\n\tCurrentPrompts  map[string]string                  // relative path -> content\n\tCurrentWorkflow string                             // .cloche file content\n\tWorkflowPath    string                             // path to .cloche file\n\tProjectDir      string\n\tWorkflowName    string\n}\n\n// Lesson is a structured insight extracted by the Reflector.\ntype Lesson struct {\n\tID              string   `json:\"id\"`\n\tCategory        string   `json:\"category\"`\n\tStepType        string   `json:\"step_type,omitempty\"`\n\tTarget          string   `json:\"target,omitempty\"`\n\tInsight         string   `json:\"insight\"`\n\tSuggestedAction string   `json:\"suggested_action\"`\n\tEvidence        []string `json:\"evidence\"`\n\tConfidence      string   `json:\"confidence\"`\n}\n\n// EvolutionResult records what an evolution pass produced.\ntype EvolutionResult struct {\n\tID             string   `json:\"id\"`\n\tProjectDir     string   `json:\"project_dir\"`\n\tWorkflowName   string   `json:\"workflow_name\"`\n\tTriggerRunID   string   `json:\"trigger_run_id\"`\n\tTimestamp      string   `json:\"timestamp\"`\n\tClassification string   `json:\"classification\"`\n\tChanges        []Change `json:\"changes\"`\n\tKnowledgeDelta string   `json:\"knowledge_delta\"`\n}\n\n// Change describes a single file modification made by evolution.\ntype Change struct {\n\tType     string `json:\"type\"`\n\tFile     string `json:\"file\"`\n\tReason   string `json:\"reason\"`\n\tSnapshot string `json:\"snapshot\"`\n}\n","numLines":57,"startLine":1,"totalLines":57}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01E6E7P2F4kS1NKDAb2ka3cz","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the two issues clearly:\n\n**Issue 1: Curator writes commentary instead of actual content**\n\nIn `curator.go`, the LLM's response (`updated`) is written directly to the file. The problem is that LLMs often return the content wrapped in markdown code fences (like ```markdown ... ``` or just ``` ... ```), with commentary before/after. The system prompt says \"Do not add commentary — return only the updated prompt content\" but LLMs don't always follow this perfectly. The fix should strip markdown code fences and surrounding commentary from the LLM response before writing it to the file.\n\n**Issue 2: New steps are added but not wired INTO the existing graph**\n\n\nIn `orchestrator.go:handleNewStep()`, the code wires outgoing edges from the new step (success to done, failure to abort), but nothing actually connects to it from the existing workflow. The new step ends up unreachable, which the validation catches as an orphaned step. I need to find an existing step that should feed into the new step—either by identifying which step currently leads to done and redirecting it, or by finding the step mentioned in the lesson data and wiring from there.\n\nNow I'm examining how the validation logic detects these orphaned steps.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6566,"cache_read_input_tokens":23100,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":6566},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0d459df6-6a73-41bb-9a61-5157dd36e9c2","uuid":"49fe355a-16e1-430e-bea7-02a3cd89a623"}
